cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.DS, cs.NE 

This paper proposes a new stacking method for regression models that uses neural networks to estimate the stacking coefficients. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions using the method for image classification (cs.CV), which suggests it could also belong to the Computer Vision sub-category. The paper also discusses the advantages of the method for datasets with large sample sizes (cs.DS) and mentions the use of neural networks (cs.NE), further supporting these sub-categories as likely options.
